WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:04:27.240 --> 00:04:30.930
[Love Between Lines]

3
00:04:31.310 --> 00:04:33.789
[Episode 2]

4
00:04:39.570 --> 00:04:43.330
♪ What identity do you use to step into and out of that role? ♪

5
00:04:44.330 --> 00:04:48.650
♪ Reality and fantasy
are parallel and intertwined ♪

6
00:04:49.370 --> 00:04:53.240
♪ Love. characters. and relationships ♪

7
00:04:50.750 --> 00:04:52.610
Everyone. welcome to Rongcheng.

8
00:04:53.310 --> 00:04:54.560
The blizzard has blocked the roads.

9
00:04:54.230 --> 00:04:58.940
♪ Like a multi-faceted gem. passionate on every page ♪

10
00:04:54.750 --> 00:04:56.030
Distinguished guests.

11
00:04:56.030 --> 00:04:58.630
you'll need to stay in Rongcheng for now.

12
00:04:59.170 --> 00:05:04.090
♪ Time and space are intertwined;
and it's still you ♪

13
00:05:04.120 --> 00:05:08.360
♪ Love brings our fates together ♪

14
00:05:05.450 --> 00:05:09.160
[15 minutes earlier]

15
00:05:08.390 --> 00:05:12.950
♪ You made me break my sudden promise ♪

16
00:05:12.980 --> 00:05:17.820
♪ Amid the sparks. two hearts slowly draw closer ♪

17
00:05:14.470 --> 00:05:16.190
This is exactly what I needed.

18
00:05:16.190 --> 00:05:17.079
Anna.

19
00:05:17.079 --> 00:05:18.810
financial adviser at Site M.

20
00:05:18.840 --> 00:05:20.310
Your mission in Rongcheng

21
00:05:20.310 --> 00:05:21.430
is to help Qin Xiaoyi

22
00:05:21.430 --> 00:05:23.400
become Rongcheng's new mayor

23
00:05:23.400 --> 00:05:24.840
and earn his trust.

24
00:05:24.960 --> 00:05:26.840
You have to beat everyone else.

25
00:05:26.840 --> 00:05:27.870
Convince Qin Xiaoyi

26
00:05:27.870 --> 00:05:29.630
to sign the policy agreement.

27
00:05:29.750 --> 00:05:30.680
However.

28
00:05:30.680 --> 00:05:32.680
you have a secret past.

29
00:05:32.800 --> 00:05:33.800
A few years ago.

30
00:05:33.800 --> 00:05:35.800
Ning Zechen saved you.

31
00:05:35.910 --> 00:05:36.840
To repay him.

32
00:05:36.840 --> 00:05:38.190
your real mission

33
00:05:38.190 --> 00:05:40.630
is to help Ning Zechen become mayor.

34
00:05:40.880 --> 00:05:43.080
The Rouge box
is your ID token.

35
00:05:43.080 --> 00:05:45.310
He'll provide evidence
to frame Qin Xiaoyi.

36
00:05:45.160 --> 00:05:48.480
♪ Healing each other ♪

37
00:05:45.310 --> 00:05:47.030
But above all. your identity

38
00:05:47.030 --> 00:05:48.750
must not be discovered by Qin Xiaoyi.

39
00:05:48.750 --> 00:05:50.410
Please proceed with caution.

40
00:06:14.750 --> 00:06:15.680
Let's go.

41
00:06:20.800 --> 00:06:21.630
Who are you?

42
00:06:22.560 --> 00:06:24.120
Let's talk. Chief Ning.

43
00:06:33.470 --> 00:06:34.560
So it really is you. Anna.

44
00:06:36.590 --> 00:06:38.190
It's been a long time. Chief Ning.

45
00:06:38.960 --> 00:06:40.560
That's all in the past.

46
00:06:40.800 --> 00:06:42.600
I'm surprised you still have it.

47
00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:43.560
Anna.

48
00:06:43.870 --> 00:06:45.280
have you been doing well abroad

49
00:06:46.120 --> 00:06:47.470
all these years?

50
00:06:48.150 --> 00:06:50.240
Do we really have to do this reunion routine?

51
00:06:53.390 --> 00:06:54.450
I've been fine.

52
00:06:56.360 --> 00:06:58.600
It's been ten years since we split up.

53
00:06:58.870 --> 00:06:59.930
On life's journey.

54
00:07:00.270 --> 00:07:03.120
we'll meet again.

55
00:07:03.480 --> 00:07:04.600
Oh. please!

56
00:07:04.600 --> 00:07:06.430
Why are you reciting poetry now?

57
00:07:08.040 --> 00:07:11.920
Let the past stay in the past.

58
00:07:17.070 --> 00:07:18.360
W-What do you mean?

59
00:07:19.800 --> 00:07:21.070
It means

60
00:07:21.100 --> 00:07:22.930
"Move on from the past."

61
00:07:23.430 --> 00:07:25.830
Hurry up and bring me proof
to pin it on Qin Xiaoyi.

62
00:07:25.830 --> 00:07:28.030
Only then can we move forward together.

63
00:07:29.270 --> 00:07:31.130
Fine. Stop talking and hand it over.

64
00:07:37.040 --> 00:07:38.440
And give me a handgun too.

65
00:07:44.440 --> 00:07:45.220
Nothing else. okay?

66
00:07:45.220 --> 00:07:45.870
Money.

67
00:07:49.190 --> 00:07:51.040
You're robbing me.

68
00:07:53.800 --> 00:07:54.600
Ms. Anna.

69
00:07:54.800 --> 00:07:56.480
I trust you.

70
00:07:56.630 --> 00:07:58.310
but if General Qin finds out about this.

71
00:07:58.310 --> 00:08:00.690
as police chief. I can't...

72
00:08:00.730 --> 00:08:01.410
Understood.

73
00:08:17.860 --> 00:08:22.540
[President's Office]

74
00:08:27.090 --> 00:08:27.550
Come in.

75
00:08:37.790 --> 00:08:39.650
I thought I'd acted too quickly.

76
00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:47.270
Which side are you on?

77
00:08:49.430 --> 00:08:51.430
You came here to steal things.

78
00:08:51.430 --> 00:08:52.870
I came here to plant flowers.

79
00:08:53.040 --> 00:08:53.970
Same objective.

80
00:08:54.390 --> 00:08:55.670
What are you talking about?

81
00:08:55.670 --> 00:08:58.380
We're each doing our own job.

82
00:08:58.410 --> 00:08:59.140
Understand?

83
00:08:59.480 --> 00:08:59.870
Listen.

84
00:08:59.870 --> 00:09:01.750
Don't tell anyone you saw us.

85
00:09:02.430 --> 00:09:03.120
Okay.

86
00:09:03.610 --> 00:09:04.410
Okay.

87
00:09:10.920 --> 00:09:11.600
What?

88
00:09:12.150 --> 00:09:13.350
Is Qin Xiaoyi coming?

89
00:09:13.770 --> 00:09:15.370
Then let's go. Now.

90
00:09:15.630 --> 00:09:16.390
Okay. okay.

91
00:09:17.270 --> 00:09:18.070
Hey...

92
00:09:18.070 --> 00:09:19.560
Is it really okay to take the phone?

93
00:09:19.560 --> 00:09:20.070
Look.

94
00:09:20.530 --> 00:09:21.460
It's just a game.

95
00:09:21.490 --> 00:09:22.680
Don't take it so seriously.

96
00:09:22.680 --> 00:09:23.510
Let's go.

97
00:09:23.800 --> 00:09:24.390
Go!

98
00:09:39.720 --> 00:09:40.480
Stop!

99
00:09:42.750 --> 00:09:43.310
What?

100
00:09:44.140 --> 00:09:44.750
Let her go!

101
00:09:44.870 --> 00:09:45.260
I...

102
00:09:48.560 --> 00:09:49.220
After them!

103
00:09:49.310 --> 00:09:49.970
After them!

104
00:10:08.660 --> 00:10:09.590
General Qin.

105
00:10:09.950 --> 00:10:12.210
don't you know how to protect your own things?

106
00:10:12.320 --> 00:10:14.030
Someone broke into your office
to steal your files.

107
00:10:14.030 --> 00:10:14.909
I tried to help.

108
00:10:14.930 --> 00:10:16.340
but was that my decision to make?

109
00:10:17.159 --> 00:10:18.000
I understand.

110
00:10:18.159 --> 00:10:19.490
You've worked very hard.

111
00:10:19.720 --> 00:10:20.390
Thank you.

112
00:10:27.720 --> 00:10:28.920
No. I can handle it myself.

113
00:10:30.600 --> 00:10:31.270
Of course.

114
00:10:44.840 --> 00:10:45.840
You two.

115
00:10:46.250 --> 00:10:47.960
go check my office.

116
00:10:48.150 --> 00:10:49.610
See if anything's missing.

117
00:10:50.270 --> 00:10:51.040
Or

118
00:10:51.940 --> 00:10:53.120
if anything new has appeared.

119
00:10:53.120 --> 00:10:53.690
Yes. sir.

120
00:11:03.030 --> 00:11:03.780
Sir.

121
00:11:04.310 --> 00:11:05.560
one document is missing.

122
00:11:05.560 --> 00:11:06.360
but

123
00:11:06.510 --> 00:11:07.970
nothing new has appeared.

124
00:11:13.539 --> 00:11:14.990
The office is a complete mess.

125
00:11:15.010 --> 00:11:16.940
He'll definitely tidy it up later.

126
00:11:17.240 --> 00:11:19.150
If I hide something here now.

127
00:11:19.390 --> 00:11:21.049
it'll be found right away.

128
00:11:21.510 --> 00:11:23.310
Not only would I fail to trap him.

129
00:11:23.440 --> 00:11:25.500
I'd become the suspect.

130
00:11:26.010 --> 00:11:26.920
Not bad.

131
00:11:27.270 --> 00:11:28.400
You just dodged a bullet.

132
00:11:28.960 --> 00:11:29.870
General Qin.

133
00:11:30.440 --> 00:11:32.640
I don't understand what you're saying.

134
00:11:32.910 --> 00:11:34.320
I'd like to invite you

135
00:11:34.320 --> 00:11:35.320
inside.

136
00:11:42.200 --> 00:11:43.260
Please. have a seat.

137
00:11:50.240 --> 00:11:51.910
Weren't your files stolen?

138
00:11:51.910 --> 00:11:53.710
Why didn't you chase them?

139
00:11:54.440 --> 00:11:55.080
There are...

140
00:11:55.080 --> 00:11:57.210
no important documents here worth stealing.

141
00:11:58.600 --> 00:12:00.320
Everything's hidden somewhere else.

142
00:12:00.320 --> 00:12:01.720
So many schemes.

143
00:12:05.270 --> 00:12:07.470
I have to admire your brains.

144
00:12:09.720 --> 00:12:11.600
Then why are you here?

145
00:12:17.920 --> 00:12:19.850
I'm Site M's financial adviser.

146
00:12:20.120 --> 00:12:22.000
I'm here to discuss an alliance with you.

147
00:12:22.000 --> 00:12:23.000
As long as

148
00:12:23.000 --> 00:12:24.460
you sign this contract...

149
00:12:26.320 --> 00:12:29.080
Once you sign...

150
00:12:34.000 --> 00:12:35.720
and the agreement is returned to M.

151
00:12:35.720 --> 00:12:38.720
the promised funds will be transferred immediately.

152
00:12:38.750 --> 00:12:39.870
General Qin. I know

153
00:12:40.080 --> 00:12:41.410
you want to be mayor.

154
00:12:41.750 --> 00:12:43.000
I can help you.

155
00:12:47.870 --> 00:12:49.400
I get what you're saying.

156
00:12:50.120 --> 00:12:52.320
but if you want me to sign this contract.

157
00:12:52.630 --> 00:12:54.560
you have to show me your sincerity.

158
00:12:56.790 --> 00:12:58.550
What kind of sincerity?

159
00:13:00.610 --> 00:13:02.400
Is this still about that formula?

160
00:13:07.960 --> 00:13:08.840
Wait!

161
00:13:12.630 --> 00:13:13.480
General Qin.

162
00:13:13.770 --> 00:13:15.130
I know what you want.

163
00:13:18.450 --> 00:13:19.450
Tonight at 10.

164
00:13:19.550 --> 00:13:20.950
meet me in the ballroom.

165
00:13:21.590 --> 00:13:22.790
Everything's ready.

166
00:13:22.840 --> 00:13:24.030
You just need one last push.

167
00:13:24.030 --> 00:13:24.960
General Qin.

168
00:13:25.320 --> 00:13:26.390
I'll give you

169
00:13:26.750 --> 00:13:27.680
that final push.

170
00:13:38.750 --> 00:13:41.480
It's like every scheme
was planned in advance.

171
00:13:41.720 --> 00:13:44.240
Last time I got the formula here too.

172
00:13:45.030 --> 00:13:46.360
Fine. I need... it.

173
00:13:46.600 --> 00:13:47.630
Stop. stop. stop!

174
00:13:47.790 --> 00:13:48.360
Stop!

175
00:13:48.870 --> 00:13:49.930
What are you doing?

176
00:13:50.610 --> 00:13:52.140
I'm stealing a letter from you!

177
00:13:59.950 --> 00:14:00.860
General Qin.

178
00:14:01.110 --> 00:14:02.920
may I have the honor of this dance?

179
00:14:03.040 --> 00:14:03.730
Sorry.

180
00:14:23.720 --> 00:14:26.450
Looks like I brought you
the wrong proof of sincerity.

181
00:14:26.860 --> 00:14:28.150
Ms. Anna.

182
00:14:37.390 --> 00:14:38.030
This

183
00:14:38.240 --> 00:14:40.840
contains the formula for making weapons.

184
00:14:40.960 --> 00:14:42.390
Before Sun Jiaying could get it.

185
00:14:42.390 --> 00:14:43.480
I intercepted it.

186
00:14:43.870 --> 00:14:44.790
General Qin.

187
00:14:44.790 --> 00:14:45.870
are you satisfied now?

188
00:14:48.120 --> 00:14:49.250
Just like we agreed.

189
00:14:49.390 --> 00:14:50.720
I'm showing you my sincerity.

190
00:14:50.750 --> 00:14:52.610
Now sign the contract with me.

191
00:14:54.510 --> 00:14:55.510
It seems you have

192
00:14:55.510 --> 00:14:57.440
some misunderstandings about me.

193
00:14:58.120 --> 00:14:58.790
I don't

194
00:14:59.000 --> 00:15:00.960
negotiate.

195
00:15:03.320 --> 00:15:05.120
Fine. That's a shame.

196
00:15:14.120 --> 00:15:15.200
General Qin.

197
00:15:15.200 --> 00:15:16.800
have you made your decision?

198
00:15:25.970 --> 00:15:28.030
General Qin. I'll take my leave.

199
00:15:37.040 --> 00:15:37.840
Take her away.

200
00:15:41.530 --> 00:15:43.480
Qin Xiaoyi. you broke your promise!

201
00:15:43.480 --> 00:15:43.880
You...

202
00:15:46.040 --> 00:15:47.850
Have I ever promised you anything?

203
00:15:50.000 --> 00:15:50.750
I know

204
00:15:51.180 --> 00:15:53.640
there are spies around me planted by others.

205
00:15:55.960 --> 00:15:56.510
Hey.

206
00:15:56.840 --> 00:15:57.750
if you don't trust me.

207
00:15:57.750 --> 00:15:59.270
why ask me for the formula?

208
00:16:00.010 --> 00:16:01.130
In war. anything goes.

209
00:16:02.310 --> 00:16:03.270
Besides.

210
00:16:03.600 --> 00:16:04.600
what have you ever given me?

211
00:16:05.010 --> 00:16:07.210
Maybe it wasn't even the real formula?

212
00:16:17.050 --> 00:16:19.290
[Revenge is only human]

213
00:16:24.510 --> 00:16:26.200
To trap me in your net.

214
00:16:26.920 --> 00:16:29.440
you've really tried hard.

215
00:16:30.720 --> 00:16:31.550
What a pity.

216
00:16:34.150 --> 00:16:35.270
General Qin...

217
00:16:35.270 --> 00:16:35.990
General Qin!

218
00:16:35.990 --> 00:16:36.680
I...

219
00:16:37.680 --> 00:16:38.370
I...

220
00:16:51.510 --> 00:16:52.600
General Qin...

221
00:16:53.700 --> 00:16:55.060
If you kill me now.

222
00:16:55.670 --> 00:16:57.480
you'll never get the formula.

223
00:16:58.200 --> 00:16:59.390
You said it yourself.

224
00:16:59.510 --> 00:17:01.240
You only focus on what you want.

225
00:17:02.040 --> 00:17:03.840
Now.

226
00:17:04.400 --> 00:17:06.460
I'm the only one who knows where it is.

227
00:17:06.980 --> 00:17:08.180
So what do you want?

228
00:17:09.130 --> 00:17:10.090
I want to live.

229
00:17:11.870 --> 00:17:13.600
So you're not a gentleman anymore?

230
00:17:14.030 --> 00:17:15.600
I can't do this alone now.

231
00:17:15.620 --> 00:17:16.410
can I?

232
00:17:20.390 --> 00:17:21.270
Eleven o'clock.

233
00:17:21.520 --> 00:17:22.680
Rongda Casino.

234
00:17:23.360 --> 00:17:24.820
This will be your last chance.

235
00:17:32.060 --> 00:17:33.350
Wait.

236
00:17:37.030 --> 00:17:37.790
No.

237
00:17:38.240 --> 00:17:39.840
He's already impatient.

238
00:17:40.480 --> 00:17:41.910
What if we wait?

239
00:17:42.480 --> 00:17:43.550
If we irritate him.

240
00:17:44.150 --> 00:17:45.240
will he just leave?

241
00:17:55.390 --> 00:17:56.600
Ms. Anna.

242
00:17:57.550 --> 00:17:59.440
please come with me.

243
00:18:01.180 --> 00:18:01.900
It's over.

244
00:18:02.190 --> 00:18:04.070
Sun Jiaying works for him.

245
00:18:04.470 --> 00:18:06.400
He's here to settle the score with me.

246
00:18:10.390 --> 00:18:11.120
Sorry.

247
00:18:11.140 --> 00:18:12.100
Ms. Anna.

248
00:18:12.800 --> 00:18:14.890
If you hand over the formula.

249
00:18:14.920 --> 00:18:16.580
maybe I can save your life.

250
00:18:18.960 --> 00:18:20.760
Chief Feng. you've misunderstood.

251
00:18:20.960 --> 00:18:22.030
You should know

252
00:18:22.030 --> 00:18:23.510
I don't have anything like that.

253
00:18:28.080 --> 00:18:29.240
Ms. Anna.

254
00:18:29.550 --> 00:18:31.810
I know you want to side with Qin Xiaoyi.

255
00:18:32.150 --> 00:18:33.790
but he's paranoid.

256
00:18:34.000 --> 00:18:35.660
He has plenty of accomplices.

257
00:18:36.120 --> 00:18:38.000
You mean nothing to him.

258
00:18:38.000 --> 00:18:38.960
Ms. Anna.

259
00:18:49.150 --> 00:18:51.610
Since you refuse to hand over the formula...

260
00:18:52.890 --> 00:18:53.930
Hang her.

261
00:18:59.180 --> 00:19:00.830
[Economic Cooperation Agreement]

262
00:18:59.990 --> 00:19:07.140
-Big!
-Small!

263
00:19:09.030 --> 00:19:09.670
Again!

264
00:19:42.099 --> 00:19:43.859
I still can't win.

265
00:20:16.270 --> 00:20:17.470
So what do you want?

266
00:20:18.510 --> 00:20:19.480
I want to live.

267
00:20:21.120 --> 00:20:22.850
So you're not a gentleman anymore?

268
00:20:22.880 --> 00:20:24.550
I can't do this alone now.

269
00:20:24.550 --> 00:20:25.440
can I?

270
00:20:35.270 --> 00:20:36.070
Ms. Anna.

271
00:20:36.550 --> 00:20:37.240
tell me—

272
00:20:37.880 --> 00:20:40.050
the formula is still with you.

273
00:20:40.050 --> 00:20:41.650
And Feng Yujin hasn't taken it.

274
00:20:57.240 --> 00:20:57.920
Of course.

275
00:21:11.490 --> 00:21:13.620
Why did you drop those candied hawthorns?

276
00:21:13.800 --> 00:21:16.200
Were you that sure I'd come save you?

277
00:21:16.920 --> 00:21:17.790
General Qin.

278
00:21:18.070 --> 00:21:20.270
I wouldn't dare bet on that.

279
00:21:22.480 --> 00:21:23.790
I dropped the hawthorns.

280
00:21:23.790 --> 00:21:25.030
Just to let you know.

281
00:21:25.550 --> 00:21:26.880
That I went to the casino

282
00:21:26.960 --> 00:21:28.560
without breaking my promise.

283
00:21:30.510 --> 00:21:31.770
Did you really have to waste that many hawthorns?

284
00:21:31.770 --> 00:21:33.770
Just to prove you went to the casino?

285
00:21:35.830 --> 00:21:36.750
Ms. Anna.

286
00:21:37.680 --> 00:21:38.810
give me the formula.

287
00:21:40.480 --> 00:21:42.940
I'll assume you're keeping your word.

288
00:21:44.640 --> 00:21:45.370
Don't worry.

289
00:21:45.400 --> 00:21:47.200
I'll take you to get it right now.

290
00:21:56.720 --> 00:21:58.240
After I got the formula.

291
00:21:58.750 --> 00:21:59.640
I hid it

292
00:21:59.640 --> 00:22:02.100
under the container next to the post office.

293
00:22:02.550 --> 00:22:05.350
The most dangerous place
is the safest place.

294
00:22:07.830 --> 00:22:08.480
Right.

295
00:22:11.550 --> 00:22:12.960
They must've followed us here.

296
00:22:12.960 --> 00:22:14.360
We need to leave. now.

297
00:22:18.640 --> 00:22:19.590
General Qin.

298
00:22:19.890 --> 00:22:21.680
please give me the formula.

299
00:22:26.520 --> 00:22:28.280
I found a document.

300
00:22:28.830 --> 00:22:29.890
but it wasn't the one

301
00:22:30.070 --> 00:22:31.680
with your name on it.

302
00:22:35.590 --> 00:22:37.200
Seems like what you want

303
00:22:37.200 --> 00:22:39.720
is more than just a simple document.

304
00:22:42.110 --> 00:22:44.570
Since you refuse to hand over the formula...

305
00:22:45.790 --> 00:22:46.720
Hang her.

306
00:22:47.640 --> 00:22:48.400
Wait!

307
00:22:56.000 --> 00:22:56.750
Chief Feng.

308
00:22:57.350 --> 00:22:59.000
I can ally with anyone.

309
00:22:59.850 --> 00:23:01.720
but the only person I want to defeat

310
00:23:01.720 --> 00:23:03.040
is Qin Xiaoyi.

311
00:23:05.000 --> 00:23:06.350
He knows I have the formula.

312
00:23:06.350 --> 00:23:08.260
He'll definitely come looking for me.

313
00:23:08.260 --> 00:23:09.910
I'll lead him to the formula.

314
00:23:11.200 --> 00:23:13.260
If you want to know where it's hidden.

315
00:23:13.660 --> 00:23:15.180
you know what you need to do.

316
00:23:17.510 --> 00:23:18.640
Interesting.

317
00:23:24.960 --> 00:23:25.920
Ms. Anna.

318
00:23:26.550 --> 00:23:27.640
well done.

319
00:23:31.720 --> 00:23:33.270
I was at the end of my rope.

320
00:23:33.510 --> 00:23:36.840
Won't you let me find a way
out of this mess?

321
00:23:38.680 --> 00:23:41.000
Finding a way out of a dead end.

322
00:23:41.000 --> 00:23:41.800
Good guts.

323
00:23:42.130 --> 00:23:43.130
I miscalculated.

324
00:23:44.640 --> 00:23:46.200
But the game isn't over yet.

325
00:23:46.480 --> 00:23:47.810
In today's match. I hope

326
00:23:48.070 --> 00:23:49.600
you'll be the one laughing last.

327
00:23:49.830 --> 00:23:50.640
I will.

328
00:23:51.600 --> 00:23:53.640
When the mayoral election comes.

329
00:23:53.660 --> 00:23:56.390
I'll invite you to sit in the audience
and watch closely.

330
00:23:56.530 --> 00:23:58.260
Who the real final winner is.

331
00:23:58.680 --> 00:24:01.240
♪ Thinking of you ♪

332
00:24:01.070 --> 00:24:01.790
Take him away.

333
00:24:01.540 --> 00:24:03.580
♪ Caring about you ♪

334
00:24:03.610 --> 00:24:05.610
♪ Good night to you ♪

335
00:24:06.200 --> 00:24:08.580
♪ For you all night long ♪

336
00:24:08.740 --> 00:24:11.080
♪ Thinking of you ♪

337
00:24:11.320 --> 00:24:13.730
♪ Caring about you ♪

338
00:24:12.200 --> 00:24:13.550
Ning Zechen and his team

339
00:24:13.550 --> 00:24:15.480
won the final victory!

340
00:24:14.220 --> 00:24:15.730
♪ Good night to you ♪

341
00:24:16.130 --> 00:24:18.700
♪ For you all night long ♪

342
00:24:19.320 --> 00:24:20.910
♪ Thinking of you ♪

343
00:24:21.290 --> 00:24:23.340
♪ Caring about you ♪

344
00:24:23.940 --> 00:24:25.940
♪ Good night to you ♪

345
00:24:26.550 --> 00:24:29.100
♪ For you all night long ♪

346
00:24:27.880 --> 00:24:28.750
Where is he?

347
00:24:29.130 --> 00:24:31.130
♪ Thinking of you ♪

348
00:24:31.310 --> 00:24:34.100
♪ For you all night long ♪

349
00:24:32.270 --> 00:24:33.110
Today is Members' Day.

350
00:24:33.110 --> 00:24:33.750
Free water.

351
00:24:33.750 --> 00:24:34.680
Help yourselves.

352
00:24:34.680 --> 00:24:37.240
Remember to replenish electrolytes
after your workout.

353
00:24:37.240 --> 00:24:38.270
What's this for?

354
00:24:38.590 --> 00:24:39.200
This?

355
00:24:39.200 --> 00:24:39.960
It's for you. Send a message

356
00:24:39.960 --> 00:24:41.440
to your favorite NPC.

357
00:24:42.160 --> 00:24:43.510
Even though we don't recommend

358
00:24:43.510 --> 00:24:44.440
players and NPCs

359
00:24:44.440 --> 00:24:45.680
having too much contact outside the game.

360
00:24:45.680 --> 00:24:47.070
you can use this method

361
00:24:47.070 --> 00:24:48.930
to show your support and love.

362
00:24:49.960 --> 00:24:51.960
So I can only show support and love?

363
00:24:51.960 --> 00:24:55.360
Writing negative comments here
is inappropriate. right?

364
00:24:59.830 --> 00:25:00.440
Thanks.

365
00:25:04.460 --> 00:25:06.240
[A fox can't be the winner here. -Anna]

366
00:25:15.640 --> 00:25:17.310
[Mr. Su]

367
00:25:38.590 --> 00:25:39.240
Mr. Su.

368
00:25:40.000 --> 00:25:42.060
Why did you suddenly cancel my leave?

369
00:25:42.070 --> 00:25:44.200
Do we have a new client?

370
00:25:44.550 --> 00:25:45.830
It's not a new client.

371
00:25:45.920 --> 00:25:46.440
We have

372
00:25:46.750 --> 00:25:48.350
a new team member joining us.

373
00:25:49.480 --> 00:25:50.810
Come here. Shuaishuai.

374
00:25:50.960 --> 00:25:51.680
Shuaishuai.

375
00:25:51.680 --> 00:25:52.920
Come here.

376
00:25:53.440 --> 00:25:55.770
I've noticed you seem pretty free every day.

377
00:25:56.070 --> 00:25:58.270
Take him to the pet salon this afternoon.

378
00:25:58.960 --> 00:26:00.160
Come on. come on.

379
00:26:01.720 --> 00:26:02.400
Okay.

380
00:26:04.830 --> 00:26:05.510
Mr. Su.

381
00:26:06.310 --> 00:26:08.640
I joined this company right after graduation.

382
00:26:09.410 --> 00:26:11.610
I originally wanted to be an architect.

383
00:26:12.000 --> 00:26:13.960
You said you needed

384
00:26:14.070 --> 00:26:16.000
an assistant who understands architecture.

385
00:26:16.000 --> 00:26:17.790
so you asked me to fill in temporarily.

386
00:26:17.790 --> 00:26:19.550
You said you'd transfer me
to the design department later.

387
00:26:19.550 --> 00:26:20.350
That's right.

388
00:26:21.510 --> 00:26:22.770
It's been three years.

389
00:26:23.240 --> 00:26:24.920
What about that transfer?

390
00:26:27.070 --> 00:26:27.830
Huh.

391
00:26:29.400 --> 00:26:30.920
That's not the right way to put it.

392
00:26:30.920 --> 00:26:32.650
I've already transferred you.

393
00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:33.860
Think about it.

394
00:26:33.940 --> 00:26:35.470
You were an assistant.

395
00:26:35.590 --> 00:26:36.440
Now?

396
00:26:36.940 --> 00:26:39.360
You're the general manager's assistant.

397
00:26:39.830 --> 00:26:40.510
Right?

398
00:26:42.750 --> 00:26:43.750
Isn't that right?

399
00:26:54.640 --> 00:26:55.270
Huh.

400
00:26:57.190 --> 00:26:58.110
The company

401
00:26:58.130 --> 00:26:59.610
doesn't have many projects right now.

402
00:26:59.610 --> 00:27:01.740
We don't need designers right now.

403
00:27:02.400 --> 00:27:03.030
Just wait until we land it.

404
00:27:03.030 --> 00:27:03.960
Another big client later this year—

405
00:27:03.960 --> 00:27:06.200
"Once we bring in a few more big clients this year.

406
00:27:06.200 --> 00:27:07.400
I'll definitely transfer you."

407
00:27:07.400 --> 00:27:09.400
"Young people shouldn't be so impatient.

408
00:27:09.400 --> 00:27:11.460
or you'll end up at a disadvantage."

409
00:27:15.520 --> 00:27:16.980
What are you trying to say?

410
00:27:17.940 --> 00:27:18.730
Nothing.

411
00:27:19.310 --> 00:27:20.510
As your assistant.

412
00:27:20.680 --> 00:27:21.750
I'll keep in mind

413
00:27:21.750 --> 00:27:23.350
everything you say.

414
00:27:26.960 --> 00:27:27.960
I'm heading out.

415
00:27:35.490 --> 00:27:36.940
I was at the end of my rope.

416
00:27:37.160 --> 00:27:39.790
Won't you let me find a way out
of this mess?

417
00:27:39.790 --> 00:27:41.160
In today's match. I hope

418
00:27:41.470 --> 00:27:43.000
you'll be the one laughing last.

419
00:27:44.400 --> 00:27:44.960
Mr. Su.

420
00:27:47.200 --> 00:27:48.110
Now what?

421
00:27:48.880 --> 00:27:49.790
I'm quitting.

422
00:27:51.200 --> 00:27:52.240
Quitting?

423
00:27:53.840 --> 00:27:55.670
Before I go. I'm warning you:

424
00:27:55.850 --> 00:27:57.750
you'd better not drink that coffee.

425
00:27:57.750 --> 00:28:00.330
Last month.
several people in our department said

426
00:28:00.330 --> 00:28:02.880
when they cleaned the coffee machine.
they found dead cockroaches.

427
00:28:02.880 --> 00:28:03.740
How many were there?

428
00:28:04.070 --> 00:28:06.160
Two or three?

429
00:28:07.880 --> 00:28:10.410
Huh—why didn't you tell me earlier?

430
00:28:14.080 --> 00:28:16.080
I think there were four. Mr. Su!

431
00:28:25.160 --> 00:28:26.000
Zhao.

432
00:28:26.000 --> 00:28:28.130
I was using it to mess with my boss...

433
00:28:28.340 --> 00:28:29.720
No. my former boss.

434
00:28:29.750 --> 00:28:31.610
Why do you actually believe that?

435
00:28:32.920 --> 00:28:33.880
Hu Xiu. how did I not notice?

436
00:28:33.880 --> 00:28:35.920
Are you seriously crazy?

437
00:28:37.480 --> 00:28:38.240
Crazy?

438
00:28:38.480 --> 00:28:39.680
I really like that title.

439
00:28:39.880 --> 00:28:41.410
Thanks for the compliment.

440
00:28:42.510 --> 00:28:45.570
So you decided to quit without lining up another job?

441
00:28:46.790 --> 00:28:48.680
You don't have any backup plan.

442
00:28:48.680 --> 00:28:52.410
It'd be much better to find a new job
before quitting.

443
00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:55.750
Zhao.

444
00:28:57.270 --> 00:29:00.670
Do you know what happens to people

445
00:29:00.920 --> 00:29:02.650
who keep looking for the best options

446
00:29:04.350 --> 00:29:05.940
with bad options on the table?

447
00:29:05.940 --> 00:29:08.200
They spend their whole lives

448
00:29:08.510 --> 00:29:09.400
without ever realizing the 'bad option'.

449
00:29:09.400 --> 00:29:10.720
So.

450
00:29:11.440 --> 00:29:12.750
I need to push myself.

451
00:29:14.160 --> 00:29:15.510
Start over.

452
00:29:16.160 --> 00:29:17.480
Start over?

453
00:29:19.590 --> 00:29:21.480
I still want to be an architect.

454
00:29:23.510 --> 00:29:24.240
Are you sure?

455
00:29:26.030 --> 00:29:27.030
Then I support you.

456
00:29:27.510 --> 00:29:29.270
With all my heart.

457
00:29:32.720 --> 00:29:34.110
You're really strong.

458
00:29:34.640 --> 00:29:36.070
And you're really weak.

459
00:29:36.920 --> 00:29:37.590
Who's that?

460
00:29:38.400 --> 00:29:39.310
Don't look.

461
00:29:39.890 --> 00:29:41.150
A murder mystery game?

462
00:29:41.290 --> 00:29:42.950
There's another session in half an hour.

463
00:29:43.790 --> 00:29:45.920
Going again? Didn't you win last time?

464
00:29:47.260 --> 00:29:49.460
Last time the fox didn't look at it.

465
00:29:49.960 --> 00:29:51.550
It wasn't a perfect win.

466
00:29:51.550 --> 00:29:52.110
I'm leaving.

467
00:29:55.960 --> 00:29:56.920
A fox?

468
00:29:58.440 --> 00:29:59.880
Is that a new character?

469
00:30:05.510 --> 00:30:06.440
This way.

470
00:30:07.810 --> 00:30:13.680
♪ Life draws the shape of my scenes ♪

471
00:30:12.720 --> 00:30:13.550
It's beautiful.

472
00:30:14.910 --> 00:30:18.390
♪ The final act
a solo in a dream ♪

473
00:30:19.590 --> 00:30:23.360
♪ Next. I drift through
the city's noise ♪

474
00:30:24.520 --> 00:30:27.580
♪ So many arrivals that became nothing ♪

475
00:30:29.010 --> 00:30:33.080
♪ I'm counting the ticks of the clock ♪

476
00:30:33.640 --> 00:30:37.580
♪ I don't know where to get off or turn back ♪

477
00:30:38.250 --> 00:30:42.540
♪ Until you walk toward me ♪

478
00:30:39.270 --> 00:30:40.330
Welcome. everyone!

479
00:30:40.920 --> 00:30:42.070
To Rongcheng.

480
00:30:51.510 --> 00:30:52.770
[Team B Warrior Commander Qin Xiaoyi]

481
00:31:04.240 --> 00:31:06.140
Rongcheng's current situation

482
00:31:06.140 --> 00:31:07.770
is very complicated.

483
00:31:09.200 --> 00:31:09.960
Chief Feng

484
00:31:10.700 --> 00:31:13.570
has already established cooperation with Pavlovich.

485
00:31:13.570 --> 00:31:16.770
Director Lin has Mr. Kobayashi's support.

486
00:31:17.110 --> 00:31:17.830
Anna.

487
00:31:18.920 --> 00:31:19.750
today.

488
00:31:20.110 --> 00:31:22.440
if we can reach an agreement

489
00:31:22.790 --> 00:31:25.680
and I get support from M headquarters.

490
00:31:26.090 --> 00:31:26.770
then I

491
00:31:28.110 --> 00:31:29.960
will definitely lead you

492
00:31:30.510 --> 00:31:32.000
to final victory.

493
00:31:36.270 --> 00:31:37.000
Anna!

494
00:31:37.390 --> 00:31:39.940
This Qin Xiaoyi is so over-the-top.

495
00:31:44.070 --> 00:31:44.960
Ms. Anna.

496
00:31:51.030 --> 00:31:51.720
Sorry.

497
00:31:51.880 --> 00:31:53.000
I'll think about

498
00:31:53.200 --> 00:31:54.110
this cooperation a little more.

499
00:31:54.110 --> 00:31:55.480
Anna. Anna!

500
00:31:55.960 --> 00:31:57.640
I don't think you understand what I'm saying.

501
00:31:57.640 --> 00:31:58.480
If you have any concerns.

502
00:31:58.480 --> 00:32:00.240
don't hesitate to speak up.

503
00:32:01.280 --> 00:32:02.680
We'll win.

504
00:32:03.590 --> 00:32:04.480
Trust me.

505
00:32:08.830 --> 00:32:09.830
This contract...

506
00:32:11.490 --> 00:32:12.580
you can take it.

507
00:32:13.000 --> 00:32:14.310
But. General Qin.

508
00:32:14.720 --> 00:32:16.110
you being so eager

509
00:32:16.320 --> 00:32:18.430
only makes me doubt your abilities.

510
00:32:26.160 --> 00:32:28.160
If you want me to sign this contract.

511
00:32:28.590 --> 00:32:30.590
you have to show me your sincerity.

512
00:32:33.130 --> 00:32:33.930
Wait a second.

513
00:32:35.550 --> 00:32:37.750
I don't understand what you're saying.

514
00:32:38.350 --> 00:32:40.750
What kind of sincerity
are you looking for?

515
00:32:47.070 --> 00:32:48.960
How many candied hawthorns
do I have to eat

516
00:32:48.960 --> 00:32:50.960
to make 600 yuan worth it?

517
00:32:53.050 --> 00:32:54.140
Let me go!

518
00:32:54.170 --> 00:32:57.080
I've been framed! I've been framed!

519
00:32:57.590 --> 00:32:58.240
Anna.

520
00:32:58.440 --> 00:32:59.970
I'm really disappointed in you!

521
00:33:00.000 --> 00:33:02.070
I'm really disappointed in you!

522
00:33:02.240 --> 00:33:03.400
Anna!

523
00:33:03.470 --> 00:33:04.710
Same here.

524
00:33:17.940 --> 00:33:18.490
Hello.

525
00:33:19.240 --> 00:33:20.590
How did today's Qin Xiaoyi show up?

526
00:33:20.590 --> 00:33:22.350
Was he different from before?

527
00:33:22.790 --> 00:33:24.310
We have two actor groups. A and B.

528
00:33:24.310 --> 00:33:25.710
They rotate.

529
00:33:25.710 --> 00:33:26.830
I see.

530
00:33:27.350 --> 00:33:29.610
Do you have schedules for both groups?

531
00:33:30.370 --> 00:33:31.240
Yes.

532
00:33:31.550 --> 00:33:33.350
but the actor you want to see

533
00:33:33.350 --> 00:33:34.770
is our special guest performer.

534
00:33:34.770 --> 00:33:36.500
His schedule isn't fixed.

535
00:33:36.770 --> 00:33:38.570
I don't know the details either.

536
00:33:39.800 --> 00:33:40.430
Take care.

537
00:33:55.270 --> 00:33:57.470
These aren't the same messages as before.

538
00:33:57.470 --> 00:33:58.470
That makes sense.

539
00:33:58.530 --> 00:34:01.460
If we don't delete them. we'll run out of space.

540
00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:30.510
Can it read my mind?

541
00:34:30.510 --> 00:34:32.770
Does anyone know Qin Xiaoyi's real name?

542
00:34:32.880 --> 00:34:34.510
All the other NPC actors
created social media accounts.

543
00:34:34.510 --> 00:34:35.920
He's the only one who stays mysterious.

544
00:34:35.920 --> 00:34:37.920
He's not even on the official cast list.

545
00:34:37.920 --> 00:34:39.510
I have a friend who works there.

546
00:34:39.510 --> 00:34:40.830
Even he couldn't find any info.

547
00:34:40.830 --> 00:34:42.750
They say he doesn't like public attention.

548
00:34:42.750 --> 00:34:43.720
He's just an NPC actor.

549
00:34:43.720 --> 00:34:44.830
It's not like he's some huge celebrity.

550
00:34:44.830 --> 00:34:45.880
Why does he have to be so mysterious?

551
00:34:45.880 --> 00:34:47.480
Maybe it's a marketing tactic.

552
00:34:47.480 --> 00:34:49.000
Tactic or not.

553
00:34:49.000 --> 00:34:50.790
the other actor really isn't that good.

554
00:34:50.790 --> 00:34:51.750
Honestly.

555
00:34:52.070 --> 00:34:53.400
he's not that great.

556
00:34:58.200 --> 00:34:58.880
Mr. Gong.

557
00:34:59.200 --> 00:35:00.800
I need to tell you something.

558
00:35:01.170 --> 00:35:03.920
Group A's Qin Xiaoyi
hasn't been coming these days.

559
00:35:03.920 --> 00:35:04.920
Today there was even a player

560
00:35:04.920 --> 00:35:07.370
who specifically asked about his sessions.

561
00:35:07.370 --> 00:35:08.850
Okay. got it.

562
00:35:11.680 --> 00:35:12.720
Hello. sir.

563
00:35:12.830 --> 00:35:14.290
Do you have a reservation?

564
00:35:14.510 --> 00:35:15.070
Yes.

565
00:35:15.530 --> 00:35:16.930
I'm waiting for a friend.

566
00:35:21.720 --> 00:35:22.310
Mr. Xiao.

567
00:35:23.270 --> 00:35:23.960
My friend.

568
00:35:24.150 --> 00:35:25.150
This way. please.

569
00:35:25.960 --> 00:35:27.490
Have you been really busy lately?

570
00:35:27.890 --> 00:35:29.750
I've been looking for apartments everywhere.

571
00:35:29.750 --> 00:35:31.640
No wonder you said you haven't been to the club.

572
00:35:31.640 --> 00:35:32.790
If you're looking for apartments. just wait.

573
00:35:32.790 --> 00:35:34.510
You can have your agent handle it.

574
00:35:34.510 --> 00:35:36.170
Why are you going in person?

575
00:35:36.920 --> 00:35:39.120
Renting there is a bit special.

576
00:35:39.880 --> 00:35:41.680
There are lots of shared places.

577
00:35:42.400 --> 00:35:45.260
Landlords want to meet tenants
before renting to them.

578
00:35:49.030 --> 00:35:49.830
What's wrong?

579
00:35:52.480 --> 00:35:53.680
I know you're busy.

580
00:35:53.870 --> 00:35:56.200
You can come to the club anytime.

581
00:35:56.310 --> 00:35:57.310
That's not it...

582
00:35:57.350 --> 00:35:58.880
An employee called me.

583
00:35:58.920 --> 00:36:00.000
He said there was a player today.

584
00:36:00.000 --> 00:36:01.200
Who specifically asked about Qin Xiaoyi?

585
00:36:01.200 --> 00:36:03.110
And the schedules for Groups A and B.

586
00:36:03.110 --> 00:36:04.970
Sounds like they came for you.

587
00:36:05.270 --> 00:36:06.880
I'll mention it.

588
00:36:07.620 --> 00:36:08.880
But Xiao. don't worry.

589
00:36:09.310 --> 00:36:11.070
When we first opened this club.

590
00:36:11.070 --> 00:36:12.270
we agreed on everything.

591
00:36:12.270 --> 00:36:13.770
It won't affect your work.

592
00:36:13.770 --> 00:36:16.270
Your schedule and information
are completely confidential.

593
00:36:16.270 --> 00:36:18.420
You won't have any personal contact with players.

594
00:36:18.420 --> 00:36:19.220
Don't worry.

595
00:36:30.440 --> 00:36:32.750
Take a good look.

596
00:36:34.240 --> 00:36:36.440
Who the real final winner is.

597
00:36:38.860 --> 00:36:42.790
[Qin Xiaoyi]

598
00:36:46.550 --> 00:36:47.949
There's no problem.

599
00:36:49.480 --> 00:36:50.320
Okay. okay.

600
00:36:52.840 --> 00:36:53.770
It's a little farther ahead.

601
00:36:58.360 --> 00:36:58.889
This way.

602
00:37:01.280 --> 00:37:02.150
Grandma Chen.

603
00:37:03.070 --> 00:37:03.880
Grandma Chen!

604
00:37:04.500 --> 00:37:06.900
I brought a client to see the apartment.

605
00:37:08.810 --> 00:37:09.480
Sorry.

606
00:37:09.960 --> 00:37:10.710
Come in.

607
00:37:18.670 --> 00:37:19.320
Thank you.

608
00:37:22.760 --> 00:37:23.110
Here. watch your step.

609
00:37:23.110 --> 00:37:23.920
It's fine.

610
00:37:25.000 --> 00:37:26.150
It's okay.

611
00:37:26.400 --> 00:37:27.960
The path's uneven. Go slowly.

612
00:37:27.960 --> 00:37:28.920
Okay. don't worry.

613
00:37:28.920 --> 00:37:29.480
Don't worry about me.

614
00:37:29.480 --> 00:37:30.070
Just hold onto your things.

615
00:37:30.070 --> 00:37:31.230
Are you here to see Xiu?

616
00:37:31.400 --> 00:37:32.130
You're back?

617
00:37:32.550 --> 00:37:33.110
Yes. yes.

618
00:37:33.840 --> 00:37:34.440
Careful.

619
00:37:35.230 --> 00:37:36.560
Where should I put this?

620
00:37:39.510 --> 00:37:40.280
Young man.

621
00:37:40.590 --> 00:37:42.650
how long are you planning to rent for?

622
00:37:43.550 --> 00:37:44.480
I haven't decided yet.

623
00:37:44.480 --> 00:37:46.010
so I'd like to rent month-to-month.

624
00:37:47.630 --> 00:37:48.630
Take your time.

625
00:37:49.760 --> 00:37:50.110
...

626
00:37:51.360 --> 00:37:52.190
Ex-father-in-law.

627
00:37:53.750 --> 00:37:54.520
Don't call us that.

628
00:37:54.520 --> 00:37:56.120
We don't deserve that title.

629
00:37:58.320 --> 00:37:59.360
Is Xiu not here?

630
00:38:00.520 --> 00:38:02.390
So you're living in this house now?

631
00:38:02.390 --> 00:38:04.100
This is all my family's property!

632
00:38:04.100 --> 00:38:06.500
Why should an outsider living here care?

633
00:38:06.960 --> 00:38:08.630
I'm just asking if she's here.

634
00:38:08.630 --> 00:38:09.830
Why are you yelling?

635
00:38:10.090 --> 00:38:10.970
Don't worry.

636
00:38:11.150 --> 00:38:13.550
Living here is very comfortable.

637
00:38:13.550 --> 00:38:15.400
All the neighbors have been here for years.

638
00:38:15.400 --> 00:38:16.510
Everyone gets along well.

639
00:38:16.510 --> 00:38:18.030
First. grab that irresponsible son.

640
00:38:18.030 --> 00:38:19.110
Make him come back to Shanghai

641
00:38:19.110 --> 00:38:20.150
and apologize in person.

642
00:38:20.150 --> 00:38:21.180
What do you mean 'irresponsible'?

643
00:38:21.180 --> 00:38:22.580
What happened to my son?

644
00:38:23.360 --> 00:38:25.070
Is breaking up irresponsible?

645
00:38:25.070 --> 00:38:26.400
These days people date.

646
00:38:26.400 --> 00:38:28.130
break up all the time. right?

647
00:38:28.710 --> 00:38:30.110
What was he doing before?

648
00:38:30.110 --> 00:38:31.760
Did he have to do this now?

649
00:38:31.760 --> 00:38:33.630
Now he hasn't come back at all.

650
00:38:33.630 --> 00:38:34.960
What kind of man is that?

651
00:38:35.070 --> 00:38:35.960
Okay. okay.

652
00:38:35.960 --> 00:38:37.160
Lower your voice.

653
00:38:37.440 --> 00:38:39.040
The neighbors are watching.

654
00:38:43.280 --> 00:38:44.000
Okay.

655
00:38:44.030 --> 00:38:44.990
in general.

656
00:38:45.020 --> 00:38:47.620
soundproofing is pretty effective. right?

657
00:38:48.630 --> 00:38:50.280
That's Mr. Hu's daughter.

658
00:38:50.420 --> 00:38:52.040
She was planning to get married.

659
00:38:52.040 --> 00:38:53.170
but for some reason.

660
00:38:53.170 --> 00:38:55.570
the groom ran off on the engagement day.

661
00:38:55.590 --> 00:38:56.440
If you ask me.

662
00:38:56.440 --> 00:38:57.350
she's right to yell at him.

663
00:38:57.350 --> 00:38:58.680
Well. Grandma.

664
00:38:58.710 --> 00:39:00.710
this is a special situation. isn't it?

665
00:39:01.590 --> 00:39:03.630
It's not usually this loud.

666
00:39:04.080 --> 00:39:05.680
It's not normally like this.

667
00:39:09.720 --> 00:39:11.650
Your son called off the engagement!

668
00:39:12.280 --> 00:39:15.110
And you have the nerve to come
to our house asking for answers?

669
00:39:15.110 --> 00:39:17.440
Do you want the first-meeting gift back?

670
00:39:17.440 --> 00:39:18.960
I've never seen anything like this.

671
00:39:18.960 --> 00:39:20.150
Let's break up peacefully.

672
00:39:20.150 --> 00:39:21.410
Split up like adults.

673
00:39:21.440 --> 00:39:22.070
What's wrong?

674
00:39:22.070 --> 00:39:23.550
You want to settle the accounts clearly?

675
00:39:23.550 --> 00:39:25.020
Or do you want everyone to decide
who's right?

676
00:39:25.020 --> 00:39:25.620
Hey!

677
00:39:25.840 --> 00:39:26.590
Mom. Dad.

678
00:39:27.400 --> 00:39:28.400
Xiu. you're here.

679
00:39:29.550 --> 00:39:30.410
Don't get angry.

680
00:39:30.440 --> 00:39:31.070
Go inside.

681
00:39:31.360 --> 00:39:32.290
I'll talk to her.

682
00:39:32.480 --> 00:39:33.400
Calm down.

683
00:39:33.400 --> 00:39:34.810
Getting angry is bad for your health.

684
00:39:34.810 --> 00:39:36.010
Go inside. now.

685
00:39:38.230 --> 00:39:39.000
Auntie.

686
00:39:39.490 --> 00:39:42.000
if you want the first-meeting gift money back.

687
00:39:42.000 --> 00:39:42.730
fine.

688
00:39:43.190 --> 00:39:44.320
But as I remember.

689
00:39:44.320 --> 00:39:46.550
when my parents first met Zhang Kran.

690
00:39:46.760 --> 00:39:48.360
they gave him a gift too.

691
00:39:48.360 --> 00:39:49.920
Based on what you gave us.

692
00:39:50.510 --> 00:39:51.550
both sides are even.

693
00:39:51.550 --> 00:39:52.940
yet today you're asking for money.

694
00:39:52.940 --> 00:39:54.340
What's the logic in that?

695
00:39:55.250 --> 00:39:56.630
Kran took it.

696
00:39:56.630 --> 00:39:57.440
It never even passed through my hands.

697
00:39:57.440 --> 00:39:59.240
What about the engagement banquet?

698
00:39:59.240 --> 00:40:00.840
Don't argue about that.

699
00:40:01.630 --> 00:40:02.850
My parents renovated the place.

700
00:40:02.850 --> 00:40:05.230
You didn't even mention the costs—fine.

701
00:40:05.230 --> 00:40:06.510
But you immediately added

702
00:40:06.510 --> 00:40:08.440
an extra table for your relatives.

703
00:40:09.080 --> 00:40:10.670
And you still have the nerve to ask her for money?

704
00:40:10.670 --> 00:40:11.200
Exactly.

705
00:40:11.800 --> 00:40:12.880
You look

706
00:40:12.880 --> 00:40:14.590
even more pathetic than I do—

707
00:40:14.760 --> 00:40:15.840
the one who got dumped.

708
00:40:16.070 --> 00:40:17.280
I have nothing to do with your son.

709
00:40:17.280 --> 00:40:18.800
Not for the rest of my life.

710
00:40:19.740 --> 00:40:21.400
But you and that kind of person

711
00:40:22.110 --> 00:40:24.370
will be tied together forever.

712
00:40:27.590 --> 00:40:28.320
Auntie.

713
00:40:28.840 --> 00:40:30.500
this is the last time I'll see you.

714
00:40:40.960 --> 00:40:43.190
If you're looking for a short-term rental.

715
00:40:43.190 --> 00:40:44.800
it is a bit of a hassle.

716
00:40:44.800 --> 00:40:46.190
As soon as I hear back from Grandma Chen.

717
00:40:46.190 --> 00:40:47.920
I'll let you know right away.

718
00:40:48.590 --> 00:40:49.190
Okay.

719
00:40:50.760 --> 00:40:51.590
Please move.

720
00:41:01.280 --> 00:41:02.280
Xiu!

721
00:41:02.760 --> 00:41:03.590
Coming.

722
00:41:12.150 --> 00:41:13.590
Oh. please.

723
00:41:13.590 --> 00:41:15.320
Control your temper. will you?

724
00:41:15.320 --> 00:41:17.070
Xiu lives here.

725
00:41:17.070 --> 00:41:18.110
If you make a scene everywhere.

726
00:41:18.110 --> 00:41:19.920
how can she keep living here?

727
00:41:19.920 --> 00:41:20.920
Exactly.

728
00:41:22.630 --> 00:41:23.550
Mom. Dad.

729
00:41:23.960 --> 00:41:24.760
Sorry.

730
00:41:25.030 --> 00:41:26.290
This is all my fault.

731
00:41:26.960 --> 00:41:28.070
That's not true.

732
00:41:28.480 --> 00:41:29.710
How could it be your fault?

733
00:41:29.710 --> 00:41:31.230
It's like walking down the street

734
00:41:31.230 --> 00:41:33.230
and stepping in dog poop someone left behind.

735
00:41:33.230 --> 00:41:35.630
You can't blame yourself for bad luck.

736
00:41:35.630 --> 00:41:36.990
We're eating here.

737
00:41:38.630 --> 00:41:39.760
Okay. I'll stop talking.

738
00:41:39.760 --> 00:41:40.280
Here.

739
00:41:40.640 --> 00:41:41.500
Have some soup.

740
00:41:41.590 --> 00:41:42.670
Come. sit.

741
00:41:45.920 --> 00:41:47.670
You need to go back to work now.

742
00:41:47.920 --> 00:41:49.590
You can't stay home on vacation forever.

743
00:41:49.590 --> 00:41:50.590
That's not right.

744
00:41:50.670 --> 00:41:51.440
Besides.

745
00:41:51.440 --> 00:41:52.510
no matter what.

746
00:41:52.670 --> 00:41:55.400
your current job is stable.

747
00:41:56.190 --> 00:41:58.070
We'll find you someone even better later.

748
00:41:58.070 --> 00:41:59.710
He'll definitely be better than that Zhang boy.

749
00:41:59.710 --> 00:42:00.220
Right?

750
00:42:00.250 --> 00:42:00.960
Dad.

751
00:42:01.550 --> 00:42:03.210
actually. I already...

752
00:42:03.320 --> 00:42:04.120
What's wrong?

753
00:42:04.480 --> 00:42:05.110
That hurts.

754
00:42:05.660 --> 00:42:08.120
I think it'll rain in a couple of days.

755
00:42:09.670 --> 00:42:11.190
What did you say?

756
00:42:11.190 --> 00:42:12.030
What's wrong?

757
00:42:13.880 --> 00:42:16.060
I've decided.

758
00:42:16.120 --> 00:42:18.560
I'm fine. I'll work hard.

759
00:42:23.550 --> 00:42:25.240
I walked my parents out.

760
00:42:25.670 --> 00:42:27.670
My mom brought you some side dishes.

761
00:42:28.000 --> 00:42:29.070
Thank her for me.

762
00:42:29.230 --> 00:42:31.360
I think they'll be at ease now.

763
00:42:32.630 --> 00:42:33.840
Did you tell them?

764
00:42:34.070 --> 00:42:35.400
About your job?

765
00:42:36.880 --> 00:42:37.840
It's fine.

766
00:42:38.030 --> 00:42:40.070
Once I find a new job in a few days.

767
00:42:40.070 --> 00:42:41.930
they won't say anything.

768
00:42:42.230 --> 00:42:44.150
I have to go to the park managers' meeting tonight.

769
00:42:44.150 --> 00:42:45.150
Let's talk later.

770
00:42:53.460 --> 00:42:58.570
♪ I watched a tram run at sunset ♪

771
00:43:01.120 --> 00:43:06.130
♪ Like walking through a pause in summer ♪

772
00:43:01.480 --> 00:43:03.840
Recalculate the distance of the glass wall.

773
00:43:03.840 --> 00:43:05.510
Send me the 3D model tomorrow.

774
00:43:07.880 --> 00:43:10.890
♪ At this moment. the sunset is gentle ♪

775
00:43:11.690 --> 00:43:14.340
♪ I look up and press the shutter ♪

776
00:43:15.710 --> 00:43:22.840
♪ I take a piece of your city as a memory ♪

777
00:43:23.590 --> 00:43:24.230
Mr. Xiao.

778
00:43:23.830 --> 00:43:28.640
♪ I take a piece of your city as a memory ♪

779
00:43:25.550 --> 00:43:26.920
The technical director is over there.

780
00:43:26.920 --> 00:43:27.630
Follow me.

781
00:43:31.030 --> 00:43:36.150
♪ I hurry off. leaving a snapshot of the dusk behind ♪

782
00:43:38.010 --> 00:43:41.360
♪ Talking about random topics ♪

783
00:43:41.600 --> 00:43:45.020
♪ Waiting for the traffic light at dusk ♪

784
00:43:46.305 --> 00:44:46.827
-== [ www.OpenSubtitles.org ] ==-
